[section#exec.scope.concepts
    [:en] Execution scope concepts
    [:zh_CN] 执行作用域概念
]

[para]
[:en] The [`:c scope_association] concept defines the requirements on a type [`Assoc].
[:zh_CN] [`:c scope_association] 概念定义针对类型 [`Assoc] 的规定。

[:en] An object of type [`Assoc] is [+engaged] if and only if it owns an
association with an async scope, referred to as its [+:adj associated[!scope]].
[:zh_CN] 当且仅当 [`Assoc] 类型的对象拥有与某个异步作用域的关联时，该对象被称为
[+已订约]，该异步作用域称为其[+:adj 关联[!作用域]]。

[codeblock:synopsis]
namespace std::execution {
  template<class Assoc>
    concept [[redoc("`:c@def>")]]scope_association =
      [[redoc("`:c>")]]movable<Assoc> &&
      is_nothrow_move_constructible_v<Assoc> &&
      is_nothrow_move_assignable_v<Assoc> &&
      [[redoc("`:c>")]]default_initializable<Assoc> &&
      requires(const Assoc assoc) {
        { static_cast<bool>(assoc) } noexcept;
        { assoc.try_associate() } -> [[redoc("`:c>")]]same_as<Assoc>;
      };
}
[codeblock:end]

[para]
[:en] A type [`Assoc] models [`:c scope_association] only if:
[:zh_CN] 仅当符合以下情况时，类型 [`Assoc] 构成 [`:c scope_association]：

[list]
[item]
[:en] a default constructed object of type [`Assoc] is not engaged;
[:zh_CN] 默认构造的 [`Assoc] 类型的对象未订约；
[item]
[:en] for an object [*assoc] of type [`Assoc], [`static_cast<bool>(assoc)] is [`true]
if and only if [`assoc] is engaged;
[:zh_CN] 对于 [`Assoc] 类型的对象 [*assoc]，当且仅当 [`assoc] 已订约时，
[`static_cast<bool>(assoc)] 为 [`true]；
[item]
[:en] no two distinct objects of type [`Assoc] own the same association;
[:zh_CN] 两个不同的 [`Assoc] 类型对象不会拥有相同的关联；
[item]
[:en] for an object [`assoc] of type [`Assoc],
destroying [`assoc] releases the association owned by [`assoc], if any;
[:zh_CN] 对于 [`Assoc] 类型的对象 [`assoc]，销毁 [`assoc] 会释放其拥有的关联（如果有）；
[item]
[:en] for an object [`assoc] of type [`Assoc], after it is used as the source
operand of a move constructor, the [`assoc] is not engaged;
[:zh_CN] 对于 [`Assoc] 类型的对象 [`assoc]，在其被用作移动构造函数的源操作数之后，[`assoc] 未订约；
[item]
[:en] for distinct objects [`assoc1] and [`assoc2] of type [`Assoc],
after evaluating [`assoc1 = std::move(assoc2)], the association owned by [`assoc1],
if any, is released and [`assoc2] is not engaged;
[:zh_CN] 对于不同的 [`Assoc] 类型对象 [`assoc1] 和 [`assoc2]，在求值
[`assoc1 = std::move(assoc2)] 之后，[`assoc1] 拥有的关联（如果有）被释放，并且 [`assoc2] 未订约；
[item]
[:en] for an object [`assoc] of type [`Assoc] that is engaged,
[`assoc.try_associate()] either returns an object that is not engaged or
acquires a new association with [`assoc][=']s associated scope and
returns an engaged object that owns that association;
[:zh_CN] 对于已订约的 [`Assoc] 类型对象 [`assoc]，[`assoc.try_associate()] 要么返回
未订约对象，要么获取与 [`assoc][=']s 关联作用域的新关联并返回拥有该关联的已订约对象；
[item]
[:en] for an object [`assoc] of type [`Assoc] that is not engaged,
[`assoc.try_associate()] returns an object that is not engaged.
[:zh_CN] 对于未订约的 [`Assoc] 类型对象 [`assoc]，[`assoc.try_associate()] 返回未订约的对象。
[list:end]

[para]
[:en] The [`:c scope_token] concept defines the requirements on a type [`Token]
that can be used to create associations between senders and an async scope.
[:zh_CN] [`:c scope_token] 概念定义针对可用于创建发送器和某个异步作用域之间的关联的
类型 [`Token] 的规定。

[:en] Every object of type [`Token] is associated with an async scope
that is referred to as its [+:% associated scope].
[:zh_CN] [`Token] 类型的每个对象都与某个异步作用域关联，该异步作用域称为其[+:% 关联作用域]。

[para]
[:en] Let [`[^test-sender]] and [`[^test-env]] be unspecified types such that
[`[`:c sender_in]<[^test-sender], [^test-env]>] is modeled.
[:zh_CN] 令 [`[^test-sender]] 和 [`[^test-env]] 为使得
[`[`:c sender_in]<[^test-sender], [^test-env]>] 得以构成的未指明类型。

[codeblock:synopsis]
namespace std::execution {
  template<class Token>
    concept [[redoc("`:c@def>")]]scope_token =
      [[redoc("`:c>")]]copyable<Token> &&
      requires(const Token token) {
        { token.try_associate() } -> [[redoc("`:c>")]]scope_association<bool>;
        { token.wrap(declval<@\placeholder{test-sender}@>()) } -> [[redoc("`:c>")]]sender_in<[[redoc("^>")]]test-env>;
      };
}
[codeblock:end]

[para]
[:en] A type [`Token] models [`:c scope_token] only if:
[:zh_CN] 仅当符合以下情况时，类型 [`Token] 构成 [`:c scope_token]：

[list]
[item]
[:en] no exceptions are thrown from copy construction, move construction,
copy assignment, or move assignment of objects of type [`Token];
[:zh_CN] [`Token] 类型对象的复制构造、移动构造、复制赋值或者移动赋值中不会抛出任何异常；

[item]
[:en] for an object [`token] of type [`Token], [`token.try_associate()] either
returns an object that is not engaged or acquires a new association with [`token][=']s
associated scope and returns an engaged object that owns that association; and
[:zh_CN] 对于 [`Token] 类型的对象 [`token]，[`token.try_associate()] 要么返回未订约对象，
要么获取与 [`token] 的关联作用域的新关联并返回拥有该关联的已订约对象；以及

[item]
[:en] given an lvalue [`token] of type (possibly const) [`Token],
for all expressions [`sndr] such that [`decltype((sndr))] models [`:c sender]:
[:zh_CN] 给定（可能 const 的）[`Token] 类型的左值 [`token]，对于所有使得
[`decltype((sndr))] 构成 [`:c sender] 的表达式 [`sndr]：

 [list]
 [item]
[:en@~] [`token.wrap(sndr)] is a valid expression,
 [item]
[:en@~] [`decltype(token.wrap(sndr))] models [`:c sender], and
 [item]
[:en@~] [`completion_signatures_of_t<decltype(token.wrap(sndr)), E>] contains
the same completion signatures as [`completion_signatures_of_t<decltype((sndr)), E>]
for all types [`E] such that [`[`:c sender_in]<decltype((sndr)), E>] is modeled.
[:zh_CN@~] 对于所有使得 [`[`:c sender_in]<decltype((sndr)), E>] 得以构成的类型 [`E]，
[`completion_signatures_of_t<decltype(token.wrap(sndr)), E>] 与
[`completion_signatures_of_t<decltype((sndr)), E>] 包含相同的完成签名。
 [list:end]
[list:end]
